  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get over a crush on my guy best friend?",
  "response": "Getting over a crush on your guy best friend can be challenging, especially when there\u2019s a close bond involved. Here are some steps to help you navigate this situation and move forward:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**\n   - It\u2019s okay to have feelings for someone, even if they\u2019re not reciprocated. Give yourself permission to feel what you\u2019re feeling without judgment.\n   - Accept that it might take time to process and move on.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Create Some Space**\n   - Spending too much time with him might make it harder to move on. Consider taking a step back to gain perspective.\n   - This doesn\u2019t mean cutting him out of your life completely, but setting boundaries can help you regain emotional balance.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Refocus Your Energy**\n   - Pour your energy into hobbies, goals, or activities that make you feel good about yourself. This can help shift your focus away from your crush.\n   - Spend time with other friends or meet new people to broaden your social circle.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Reevaluate the Relationship**\n   - Remind yourself why being friends is valuable and why a romantic relationship might not work. Focus on the positive aspects of your friendship.\n   - If he\u2019s not interested in you romantically, try to accept that reality rather than holding onto hope.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Talk to Someone You Trust**\n   - Venting to a trusted friend or family member can help you process your emotions and gain clarity.\n   - If you\u2019re struggling to cope, consider speaking with a therapist or counselor.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Avoid Romanticizing the Situation**\n   - It\u2019s easy to idealize someone you have feelings for. Challenge those thoughts by reminding yourself of his flaws or why he might not be the best match for you.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Give Yourself Time**\n   - Healing from unrequited feelings takes time. Be patient with yourself and trust that the intensity of your emotions will fade.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Consider the Friendship**\n   - If your feelings are too strong and being around him is painful, you may need to take a longer break from the friendship.\n   - Ultimately, prioritize your emotional well-being.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Focus on Self-Growth**\n   - Use this experience as an opportunity to learn more about yourself, your needs, and what you want in a future partner.\n   - Build confidence in your independence and self-worth.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Let Go of What You Can\u2019t Control**\n   - You can\u2019t control your feelings, but you can control how you respond to them. Focus on what\u2019s within your power, like how you choose to spend your time and energy.\n\n---\n\nRemember, it\u2019s normal to feel disappointed, but this experience can lead to personal growth and a deeper understanding of yourself. You\u2019ll eventually find someone who reciprocates your feelings, and your friendship with your best friend may even grow stronger in the process.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
